OL,3,CJail sentences handed out to those
OL,4,Cinvolved in Southampton disorder
OL,6,FO'Leary, from Basingstoke, was jailed
OL,7,Ffor three years and one month for
OL,8,Fviolent disorder, obstructing a
OL,9,Fconstable and possessing an offensive
OL,10,Fweapon.
OL,12,FPolice footage caught him throwing a
OL,13,Fsmoke grenade at officers during the
OL,14,Fdisorder.
OL,16,FConnor Bishop, 24
OL,18,FBishop from Southampton was jailed for
OL,19,Ftwo years and eight months for violent
OL,20,Fdisorder.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
